headline: 2 Growth Stocks Down Over 25% to Buy Before They Soar
summary: Celsius Holdings (NASDAQ: CELH) is an emerging brand in a $200 billion energy drink market.  Fourth-quarter revenue was down 4% year over year, but most importantly, retail sales of Celsius' products grew 22%, significantly outpacing the total energy drink category.  The strong sales volumes indicate Celsius is well positioned for long-term growth.
